THOUGHT: The crash persists because InstructionsState::getOpcode still calls getMainOp(), triggering the assert when the state is invalid. I will update getOpcode to avoid calling getMainOp and instead use MainOp directly with a valid() check. I will also guard TreeEntry::isOneOf to avoid calling S.getMainOp when invalid. Then I will rerun opt to verify the fix.

```bash
awk 'BEGIN{go=0} 
/unsigned getOpcode\(\) const \{/ {print; go=1; next} 
go==1 && /return getMainOp\(\)->getOpcode\(\);/ {print "    return valid() ? MainOp->getOpcode() : 0;"; go=0; next} 
{print}' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp > /tmp/SLPVectorizer.cpp.p1 && mv /tmp/SLPVectorizer.cpp.p1 llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp && sed -i "s/return S.getMainOp();/return S.valid() ? S.getMainOp() : Op;/" llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp && /llvm-autofix/build/llvm-build/129242/bin/opt -S --passes=slp-vectorizer -mtriple=x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu /tmp/test.ll
```

